Inside of Brian's brain, as the tumor ate away the very fabric of his reality, he slipped into a dream like an old VHS, wet with the grey glitter of time's shadow, a story unfolding in the warbling pace of elastic magnetic tape.  Heand his family knew he would die soon, so his fantasies within had become his salvation from a depressing fate of mortality. The machines, his constant companions, pumped life into him and a synchronized symphony of noises and their accompanying hallucinatory melodies and voices. Our story begins on the day of his death….
